  "prompt": "Who are some famous INFJs?",
  "response": "INFJ is one of the sixteen personality types classified by the Myers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI). People with this personality type are often described as idealistic, insightful, empathetic, and creative. Some famous individuals believed to be INFJs include:\n\n1. **Martin Luther King Jr.** - Civil rights leader who played a pivotal role in the American civil rights movement.\n2. **Mother Teresa** - Known for her humanitarian work and founding the Missionaries of Charity.\n3. **Nelson Mandela** - Anti-apartheid revolutionary and former President of South Africa.\n4. **Gandhi** - Leader of Indian independence movement and advocate for nonviolent resistance.\n5. **Nicole Kidman** - Award-winning actress known for her work in both Hollywood and independent films.\n6. **Fyodor Dostoevsky** - Renowned Russian novelist and philosopher.\n7. **Carl Jung** - Influential psychiatrist and psychoanalyst who founded analytical psychology.\n8. **Florence Nightingale** - Pioneer of modern nursing and public health advocate.\n9. **Jimmy Carter** - 39th President of the United States and Nobel Peace Prize laureate.\n10. **Tolkien** - Author of \"The Lord of the Rings\" and \"The Hobbit.\"\n\nRemember that assessment of a personality type, especially for historical or public figures, often involves a degree of speculation and interpretation based on their known behaviors and actions.",
